rComments: Professor simply reads slides from PowerPoint, word for word. The material does not seem overly hard up to date. Exams are ridiculous, consisting of 100 questions in 80 minutes, which doesn't give time to think or even thoroughly read them in many cases. She is still a young teacher with potential but needs to be more logical in her exam format.

Fantastic professor, incredibly organized and gives great feedback. But be warned - this is NOT an easy course. She makes you WORK for it. Be prepared to spend lots of your time on weekly assignments with a chance of getting it all wrong. I just dropped it because I don't have time for my "easy elective" to take more work than my mandatory classes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']
